# Agent Memory Protocol

${marker}

This repository uses the Agent Field Kit memory protocol. Engramize is the
preferred local scaffold for qualification, deduplication, drafting, approval,
and verification of durable agent memories.

## Rules

- Search existing memory before preserving a new lesson.
- Prefer focused chunks over full-memory reads when a chunk is enough.
- Do not store secrets, credentials, private account data, or raw user tokens.
- Draft memory entries first; commit them only after explicit approval.
- Store durable technical lessons, project decisions, environment constraints,
  and repeatable workflows.
- Skip one-off observations, noisy logs, and facts already captured elsewhere.

## Suggested Workflow

1. Qualify the candidate lesson.
2. Search for semantic duplicates.
3. Draft a concise memory with title, tags, evidence, and verification notes.
4. Ask for approval before committing.
5. Verify the committed memory can be found again.

